8.4 UNderstanding RHEL 8 Networking

the config file for the ens33 NIC is located at /etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/cfg-ens33

to manage this, you can use network manager

nmcli is one way to do this, you can also use nmtui. Both of these edit the configs for you. You can also directly edit the file

The ip command is great for troubleshooting because you can make non permanent changes